Leeco Diagnostics Inc saidthe National Institutes of Health have awarded it a two-year,478,568 dlr federal grant to develop a new medical test kit todiagnose and monitor diabetes mellitus.    Leeco said the Institutes made the grant under their smallbusiness innovation research program.    The company said the research, beginning April 1, willfocus on developing a more effective technique for detectinghemoglobin A1C in the blood. High levels of hemoglobin A1C canindicate uncontrolled diabetes. Reuter&#3;